  (text "UNO Q HUB75 SHIELD — Rev 0.3 — BLOCK DIAGRAM\\n\\nSignal flow (IEEE 315: left to right, power top to bottom):\\n\\n  J4 (+5V_EXT) → [POWER] → +3V3 (AMS1117) +5V_EXT_HUB75 (direct)\\n  J2 (UNO Q JSPI) → [UNO Q INTERFACE] → SPI3 slave to ESP32-S3\\n  [ESP32-S3] → HUB75 GPIO → [HUB75 DRIVER] → J1 IDC → Panel\\n  [ESP32-S3] → I2S → [AUDIO CODEC] → J_OUT line-out / J_MIC mic\\n  [ESP32-S3] → SPI2 + I2C → [DISPLAY] → J6 FPC → 5in TFT + GT911\\n  [UNO Q MCU] → I2C → [CONNECTIVITY] → J8/J9 Qwiic J10-J14 Grove\\n\\nSub-sheets:\\n  sheets/power.kicad_sch          AMS1117-3.3 LDO FB1 ferrite indicators\\n  sheets/esp32s3.kicad_sch        ESP32-S3-WROOM-1-N16R8 USB-C debug\\n  sheets/hub75_driver.kicad_sch   SN74HCT245 x2 HUB75 IDC OE tied LOW\\n  sheets/audio_codec.kicad_sch    ES8388 AGND star DC-block caps\\n  sheets/display.kicad_sch        22-pin FPC SPI2 GT911 touch BL PWM\\n  sheets/uno_q_interface.kicad_sch  J2 SPI3 J3 UART debug\\n  sheets/connectivity.kicad_sch   Qwiic x2 Grove x5"
